#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:3
msgid "Ad hoc shell environments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:5
msgid ""
"In a Nix shell environment, you can immediately use any program packaged "
"with Nix, without installing it permanently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:7
msgid ""
"You can also share the command invoking such a shell with others, and it "
"will work on all Linux distributions, WSL, and macOS[^1]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:11
msgid "Create a shell environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:13
msgid ""
"Once you {ref}`install Nix <install-nix>`, you can use it to create new "
"*shell environments* with programs that you want to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:15
msgid ""
"In this section you will run two exotic programs called `cowsay` and "
"`lolcat` that you will probably not have installed on your machine:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:17
msgid ""
"$ cowsay no can do\n"
"The program ‘cowsay’ is currently not installed.\n"
"\n"
"$ echo no chance | lolcat\n"
"The program ‘lolcat’ is currently not installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:25
msgid ""
"Use `nix-shell` with the `-p` (`--packages`) option to specify that we need "
"the `cowsay` and `lolcat` packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:28
msgid ""
"The first invocation of `nix-shell` for these packages may take a while to "
"download all dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:31
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p cowsay lolcat\n"
"these 3 derivations will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/zx1j8gchgwzfjn7sr4r8yxb7a0afkjdg-builder.pl.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/h9sbaa2k8ivnihw2czhl5b58k0f7fsfh-lolcat-100.0.1.drv\n"
"  ...\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:41
msgid ""
"Within the Nix shell, you can use the programs provided by these packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:43
msgid "[nix-shell:~]$ cowsay Hello, Nix! | lolcat\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:47
msgid ""
"Type `exit` or press `CTRL-D` to exit the shell, and the programs won't be "
"available anymore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:49
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ exit\n"
"exit\n"
"\n"
"$ cowsay no more\n"
"The program ‘cowsay’ is currently not installed.\n"
"\n"
"$ echo all gone | lolcat\n"
"The program ‘lolcat’ is currently not installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:60
msgid "Running programs once"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:62
msgid "You can go even faster, by running any program directly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:64
msgid "$ nix-shell -p cowsay --run \"cowsay Nix\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:68
msgid "If the command consists only of the program name, no quotes are needed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:70
msgid "$ nix-shell -p hello --run hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:74
msgid "Search for packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:76
msgid ""
"What can you put in a shell environment? If you can think of it, there's "
"probably a Nix package of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:80
msgid ""
"Enter the program name you want to run in [search.nixos.org](https://search."
"nixos.org/packages) to find packages that provide it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:83
msgid "For the following example, find the package names for these programs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:85
msgid "`git`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:86
msgid "`nvim`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:87
msgid "`npm`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:89
msgid ""
"In the search results, each item shows the package name, and the details "
"list the available programs.[^2]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:94
msgid "Run any combination of programs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:96
msgid ""
"Once you have the package name, you can start a shell with that package. The "
"`-p` (`--packages`) argument can take multiple package names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:99
msgid ""
"Start a Nix shell with the packages providing `git`, `nvim`, and `npm`. "
"Again, the first invocation may take a while to download all dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:102
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p git neovim nodejs\n"
"these 9 derivations will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/7gz8jyn99kw4k74bgm4qp6z487l5ap06-packdir-start.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/d6fkgxc3b04m85wrhg6j0l5y0ray82l7-packdir-opt.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/da6njv7r0zzc2n54n2j54g2a5sbi4a5i-manifest.vim.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/zs4jb2ybr4rcyzwq0dagg9rlhlc368h6-builder.pl.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/g8sl2xnsshfrz9f39ki94k8p15vp3xd7-vim-pack-dir.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/jmxkg8b1psk52awsvfziy9nq6dwmxmjp-luajit-2.1.0-2022-10-04-env."
"drv\n"
"  /nix/store/kn83q8yk6ds74zgyklrjhvv5wkv5wmch-python3-3.10.9-env.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/m445wn3vizcgg7syna2cdkkws3kk1gq8-neovim-ruby-env.drv\n"
"  /nix/store/r2wa882mw99c311a4my7hcis9lq3kp3v-neovim-0.8.1.drv\n"
"these 151 paths will be fetched (186.43 MiB download, 1018.20 MiB "
"unpacked):\n"
"  /nix/store/046zxlxhq4srm3ggafkymx794bn1jksc-bzip2-1.0.8\n"
"  /nix/store/0p1jxcb7b4p8jhhlf8qnjc4cqwy89460-unibilium-2.1.1\n"
"  /nix/store/0q4fpnqmg8liqraj7zidylcyd062f6z0-perl5.36.0-URI-5.05\n"
"  ...\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:124
msgid "Check package versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:126
msgid ""
"Check that you have the specific version of these programs provided by Nix, "
"even if you had any of them already installed on your machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:128
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ which git\n"
"/nix/store/3cdi52xh6lk3h1fb51jkxs3p561p37wg-git-2.38.3/bin/git\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ git --version\n"
"git version 2.38.3\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ which nvim\n"
"/nix/store/ynskzgkf07lmrrs3cl2kzr9ah487lwab-neovim-0.8.1/bin/nvim\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ nvim --version | head -1\n"
"NVIM v0.8.1\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ which npm\n"
"/nix/store/q12w83z0i5pi1y0m6am7qmw1r73228sh-nodejs-18.12.1/bin/npm\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ npm --version\n"
"8.19.2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:148
msgid "Nested shell sessions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:150
msgid ""
"If you need an additional program temporarily, you can run a nested Nix "
"shell. The programs provided by the specified packages will be added to the "
"current environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:153
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ nix-shell -p python3\n"
"this path will be fetched (11.42 MiB download, 62.64 MiB unpacked):\n"
"  /nix/store/pwy30a7siqrkki9r7xd1lksyv9fg4l1r-python3-3.10.11\n"
"copying path '/nix/store/pwy30a7siqrkki9r7xd1lksyv9fg4l1r-python3-3.10.11' "
"from 'https://cache.nixos.org'...\n"
"\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ python --version\n"
"Python 3.10.11\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:163
msgid "Exit the shell as usual to return to the previous environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:166
msgid "Towards reproducibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:168
msgid ""
"These shell environments are very convenient, but the examples so far are "
"not reproducible yet. Running these commands on another machine may fetch "
"different versions of packages, depending on when Nix was installed there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:171
msgid ""
"What do we mean by reproducible? A fully reproducible example would give "
"exactly the same results no matter when or where you run the command. The "
"environment provided would be identical each time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:175
msgid ""
"The following example creates a fully reproducible environment. You can run "
"it anywhere, anytime to obtain the exact same version of the `git`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:178
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p git --run \"git --version\" --pure -I nixpkgs=https://github."
"com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tarball/2a601aafdc5605a5133a2ca506a34a3a73377247\n"
"...\n"
"git version 2.33.1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:184
msgid "There are three things going on here:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:186
msgid ""
"`--run` executes the given [Bash command](https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/"
"manual/bash.html#Shell-Commands) within the environment created by Nix, and "
"exits when it's done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:188
msgid ""
"You can use this with `nix-shell` whenever you want to quickly run a program "
"you don't have installed on your machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:190
msgid ""
"`--pure` discards most environment variables set on your system when running "
"the shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:192
msgid ""
"It means that only the `git` provided by Nix is available inside that shell. "
"This is useful for simple one-liners such as in the example. While "
"developing, however, you will usually want to have your editor and other "
"tools around. Therefore we recommend to omit `--pure` for development "
"environments, and to add it only when the extra isolation is needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:197
msgid "`-I` determines what to use as a source of package declarations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/first-steps/ad-hoc-shell-environments.md:199
msgid ""
"Here we provided [a specific Git revision of `nixpkgs`](https://github.com/"
"NixOS/nixpkgs/tree/2a601aafdc5605a5133a2ca506a34a3a73377247), leaving no "
"doubt about which version of the packages in that collection will be used."
msgstr ""

